Hi there,

[https://www.figma.com/legal/tos/] for our Starter and Professional plans. We do
this regularly to ensure these terms are clear and cover the growing list
of products, features, and services available to you as a Figma user. We’ve also
updated our terms to stay current with applicable laws and regulations and to
add clarity where we believe it would be useful.

You can currently view both the existing and new Terms of Service here

subject: Just dropped: 340+ sessions for AWS Summit Washington, DC
body:
Innovation starts here
----------------------------------

Discover what's next in cloud and AI at AWS Summit Washington, DC https://email.awscloud.com/MTEyLVRaTS03NjYAAAGaz9qN-0RPE-rt3J2HExd_imqApGS29HY2Bi7TaZPEcB5Pc6AWbhE-b1-OH4TTGOCaME5cE-s= on June 10-11. Learn from customer success stories, connect with AWS Partners, and get direct access to AWS experts—all at no cost. Join thousands of innovators ready to transform their possibilities with AWS.

Save your spot https://email.awscloud.com/MTEyLVRaTS03NjYAAAGaz9qN_OE5gqXGXOfeJv8ej5-s-dbuK7dvMaTgrTdLWQtepiAusPuarW5-W7DUkqo0NNQHqE8=

Most anticipated sessions:

AWS Summit Keynote
Join Dave Levy, Vice President of Worldwide Public Sector and Healthcare and Life Sciences North America, to learn about the latest innovations in AWS compute, storage, and generative AI. Hear from government, education, and healthcare leaders as they share how they're harnessing cloud innovations to transform mission delivery.

Building safer skies: FAA raises aviation safety with Amazon Bedrock | AIM102 
Join us to discover how the Federal Aviation Administration is leveraging AI on Amazon Bedrock to transform aviation safety.

From big data to big change: Building AI solutions for global reach | NPR203 
Learn how organizations can transform their knowledge base into an accessible, 24/7 digital resource using AWS's advanced capabilities, including generative AI.

Innovation at scale with new AWS GovCloud(US) capabilities | GVC305 
We'll examine how AWS GovCloud (US)'s latest capabilities and planned offerings drive innovation in sovereign and regulated cloud computing.

Our curated attendee guide https://email.awscloud.com/MTEyLVRaTS03NjYAAAGaz9qN-4xyA2hYg1zdcS5K5t3KXrGZw49_AYT69fxhObHuBWLCjapaqqn5K_wJhf0SD54PtEk= makes it easy to plan your schedule and discover sessions, activations, and networking opportunities tailored for you.

Interactive activations in Expo:

GenAI hub: Step into the new GenAI Hub, an innovative space showcasing the latest advancements in artificial intelligence. Experience hands-on demos at the Builders' Bench, explore interactive Content Kiosks, and visit the Sports Corner highlighting AI implementations with partners like F1, NFL, and PGAT.

AWS Training and Certification hub: Learn from AWS experts about how AWS Training and Certification can help you gain practical experience with real-world cloud scenarios, validate your cloud expertise, and much more.

Dev chats: Join us for 30 minute community-led sessions where attendees hear directly from AWS customers and AWS Heroes about how they are innovating, expediting, and scaling real-world solutions.

This is a complimentary event. Don't miss the chance to invest in professional development for your whole team.

subject: Build stronger cloud security skills at AWS re:Inforce
body:
Unlock new skills in cloud security

Strengthen your cloud security skills with practical workshops at AWS re:Inforce 2025. Participate in interactive labs focused on solving real security challenges, including threat detection in containerized environments and automated compliance verification.

Learn implementation techniques for permission boundaries, security incident response automation, and multi-account security controls from AWS experts and experienced practitioners. Return with actionable approaches to improve your organization's security posture and reduce incident response time.

Use code secure150off at checkout to save $150 on your full conference pass.

Register now
https://reinforce.awsevents.com/?trk=718b013f-1789-49c6-8906-6ab44558152c&sc_channel=em

----------
Master next-gen security architecture
Join security engineers and developers for technical sessions focused on real-world implementation and architecture. Build working solutions for zero trust architectures, container security, and automated compliance verification on AWS. Apply infrastructure-as-code security patterns through guided workshops that provide step-by-step guidance.

Figma

Join the Figma student
community ( https://www.figma.com/education/students/?utm_source=figma&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=student_onboarding&utm_content=d3_header&utm_campaign=Onboarding+-+Ed&utm_content=Day+03+-+Edu+Co&utm_medium=email&utm_source=figma )

************************
Learn from the community
************************

One of the best ways to learn Figma and level-up your skills is by getting involved in the community. Here are a few ways you can get started:

* Prepare for a career in Design ( https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLXDU_eVOJTx5XxU4ncwRmFKjXQhpRU0Cr&utm_campaign=Onboarding+-+Ed&utm_content=Day+03+-+Edu+Co&utm_medium=email&utm_source=figma ): Catch up on the Figma for Education early careerВ livestream series, including a high-level overview of the design hiring process (how design teams are structured, how to create a strong portfolio, and more) with the Figma Product Design team.
* Sign up for a Figma event ( https://www.figma.com/events/?utm_source=figma&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=student_onboarding&utm_content=d3_events&utm_campaign=Onboarding+-+Ed&utm_content=Day+03+-+Edu+Co&utm_medium=email&utm_source=figma ): Register for upcoming live Figma events, including free monthly education workshops for students.
* Explore the Figma Community ( https://www.figma.com/community/explore?utm_source=figma&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=student_onboarding&utm_content=d3_community&utm_campaign=Onboarding+-+Ed&utm_content=Day+03+-+Edu+Co&utm_medium=email&utm_source=figma ): Browse thousands of templates published by professional designers.

That's all for now. We're here if you get stuck or have questions. :)

Education plan ( https://www.figma.com/education/students/?utm_source=figma&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=student_onboarding&utm_content=d1_header&utm_campaign=Onboarding+-+Ed&utm_content=Day+01+-+Edu+We&utm_medium=email&utm_source=figma )

************************************
Welcome to the Figma Education plan!
************************************

We're so glad to have you. Here are a few resources to help you make the most out of Figma:

Figma templates
Figma connects everyone in the design process so teams can deliver better products, faster. These are some of our favorite templates to get started with Figma:

* Resume template ( https://www.figma.com/community/file/1010660375106013895?utm_source=figma&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=student_onboarding&utm_content=d1_resume&utm_campaign=Onboarding+-+Ed&utm_content=Day+01+-+Edu+We&utm_medium=email&utm_source=figma ): Easily create and update your resume in Figma.
* Portfolio examples ( https://www.figma.com/community/search?model_type=hub_files&q=portfolio&utm_campaign=Onboarding+-+Ed&utm_content=Day+01+-+Edu+We&utm_medium=email&utm_source=figma ): Get inspired by portfolios in the Figma Community.
* Feedback and critique template ( https://www.figma.com/community/file/1004815470827503480?utm_source=figma&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=student_onboarding&utm_content=d1_feedback&utm_campaign=Onboarding+-+Ed&utm_content=Day+01+-+Edu+We&utm_medium=email&utm_source=figma ): Facilitate constructive feedback from teachers and peers.

FigJam templates
FigJam is an online whiteboard for teams to brainstorm and ideate together. These templates will help you start jamming on your next project faster:

* Diagramming basics ( https://www.figma.com/community/file/1009957993740460488?utm_source=figma&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=student_onboarding&utm_content=d1_diagramming&utm_campaign=Onboarding+-+Ed&utm_content=Day+01+-+Edu+We&utm_medium=email&utm_source=figma ): Build your next flow chart with flexible connectors and shortcuts.
* User research resources ( https://www.figma.com/community/file/1012167783518516251?utm_source=figma&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=student_onboarding&utm_content=d1_research&utm_campaign=Onboarding+-+Ed&utm_content=Day+01+-+Edu+We&utm_medium=email&utm_source=figma ): Easily create user personas and consolidate research findings.
* Mood boarding activity ( https://www.figma.com/community/file/1009126889310374966?utm_source=figma&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=student_onboarding&utm_content=d1_moodboards&utm_campaign=Onboarding+-+Ed&utm_content=Day+01+-+Edu+We&utm_medium=email&utm_source=figma ): Create fun mood boards before starting your next project.

Explore all templates ( https://www.figma.com/community/explore?utm_source=figma&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=student_onboarding&utm_content=d1_main_button&utm_campaign=Onboarding+-+Ed&utm_content=Day+01+-+Edu+We&utm_medium=email&utm_source=figma )

That's all for now. We're here if you get stuck or have questions. :)

subject: Welcome to Figma!
body:
Welcome to Figma!

We're so glad you're here. Over the next few weeks, we'll share tips to help you
make the most of Figma. To get started, create a new file
[https://figma.com/new], begin with a template
[https://www.figma.com/community/design-templates?resource_type=files&editor_type=figma&price=free],
or check out the resources and features below.

Create a file [https://figma.com/new]

Learn key features in Figma with our official guides
[https://static.figma.com/uploads/ed644d88dde0ab3dee098050e9fb80ffac459d04]https://www.figma.com/community/collections/playground


GETTING STARTED GUIDES

FIGMA ENABLES INDUSTRY EXPERTS AND FIRST-TIME DESIGNERS ALIKE TO DESIGN WITH
EASE. SPIN UP ON KEY FEATURES WITH OUR OFFICIAL WALKTHROUGH GUIDES.

View the guides → [https://www.figma.com/community/collections/playground]

Find the best template for your project
[https://static.figma.com/uploads/3d1baaa1cc54e788d1b03a6b88dd8958f532b2a6]
https://www.figma.com/community/design-templates?resource_type=files&editor_type=figma&price=free

Apply for $300 AWS Credits today

Based on the qualifications of your profile, you have been invited to apply for $300 in AWS credits . At AWS, we are dedicated to helping our customers find the right products and services to help them grow and scale their businesses. 
 
We want to help you build out a proof of concept that works for your business. Apply for credits to help you get started on your project. If your application is approved, the credits will be applied directly into your AWS Account.


Apply today

Cost Optimization with AWS

You can seamlessly scale up and down with AWS to operate more cost effectively and better position your organization for long-term success.

subject: Develop your AWS expertise
body:
Technical skills and cloud expertise grow your career

Prove your cloud expertise with industry-recognized certifications

AWS Training and Certification  helps you build and validate your cloud skills to get more out of the cloud.

 - Learn from AWS experts to improve your skills and knowledge
 - Leverage the AWS Cloud for your career

Learn more about AWS Certification 
You can earn an AWS Cloud Essentials Digital Badge after passing the online assessment at the end of the learning plan.



Enroll in a learning plan/earn a digital badge › 
Cloud Practitioner Fundamentals
Free digital training to learn basic cloud concepts, services, pricing, and support.

Get started with AWS Cloud Practitioner Essentials ›  


Learning paths by role or solution
Choose a role or solution to get recommendations for classes, learning plans, and resources.

See next steps › 


Still have questions about training? 
Contact us ›

subject: Understanding your first AWS costs
body:
Start tracking your AWS costs and usage

Explore your AWS costs and usage

Stay up-to-date with your resource deployment and cost optimization opportunities.
Get started with AWS Cost Explorer 

If you're new to AWS, or just want to brush up on best practices, start with these resources:


Keep your spend in check with custom budget threshold and auto alert notification.
AWS Budgets › 
Leverage free trials and programmatic discounts based on your workload needs.
AWS Free Tier › 
You can use AWS Free Tier usage alerts to track and take action on your cost and usage.
How to check if you are exceeding the AWS Free Tier limits › 
Run latency sensitive applications closer to end users with pay-as-you go pricing with AWS Local Zones.  
See what AWS Local Zones offer ›

subject: Getting started with AWS Cost Anomaly Detection - Ade (864981742660)
body:
AWS Account: Ade (864981742660)
            







                    Hello,
                






                    As part of your enablement of AWS Cost Explorer, we have configured AWS Cost Anomaly Detection for your account. Cost Anomaly Detection is a cost management service that helps you reduce cost surprises and enhance control without slowing innovation. It uses advanced machine learning models to detect and alert on anomalous spend patterns across your deployed AWS services. The cost monitor and daily email alert subscription we set up for you are free. You can change the default configuration via our console or API to customize the alerts you receive. You can also configure immediate alerts via SNS, though additional charges for using SNS may apply.
                






                    To get you started with AWS Cost Anomaly Detection, we pre-configured your account with an AWS Services monitor and a daily summary alerting subscription. With this setup, you will be alerted about anomalous spend that exceeds $100 and 40% of your expected spend across the majority of your AWS services in your accounts. See limitations here. If you want to modify your monitor or alert subscription setting, you can visit the Cost Anomaly Detection console or the public API to configure your cost monitors and alerting subscriptions to your specific needs. You can read more about how to use the service in our announcement blog, on our product page, and in our documentation.
                







                    FAQ:
                






                    Q: Why am I receiving this email?
                



                    In an effort to help our customers detect unintended spend, we are enabling Cost Anomaly Detection for all our new AWS Cost Explorer customers. This email is associated with your AWS account. If you are not interested in this service, you can opt-out by deleting your monitor and subscription in the console or via the API
            





                    Q: What is Cost Anomaly Detection?
                



                    Cost Anomaly Detection is an AWS cost management service that monitors customers’ spend continuously, uses machine learning to detect anomalies, and generates alerts with root cause analysis of what caused the anomaly. With the service, you can reduce unplanned spend and minimize time and resources in triaging root causes. You can read more about the service on our product page and in our documentation.
                






                    Q: What is the pricing of Cost Anomaly Detection?
                



                    There is no charge for Cost Anomaly Detection. The cost monitor and daily email alert subscription we set up for you are free. You can change the default configuration via our console or API to customize the alerts you receive. You can also configure immediate alerts via SNS, though additional charges for using SNS may apply.
                






                    Q: What type of anomalies will Cost Anomaly Detection detect?
                



                    With the default setup, Cost Anomaly Detection will monitor costs on the majority of your AWS services in your accounts. See limitations here.
                






                    Q: How will I be alerted about anomalies?
                



                    Any anomalous spend related to your account(s) will show up in the Cost Anomaly Detection console and via the API. In addition, if the anomaly is above $100 and exceeds 40% of expected spend, you will receive a daily summary email to the primary email associated with your account, detailing the cost impact, account name, the name of the monitor, the start and end dates, and the service where it was observed. The email will also include potential root causes for the anomaly.
                






                    Q: How do I opt out?
                



                    If you are not interested in this service, you can opt-out by deleting your monitor(s) and subscription(s) in the console or via the API. Read more in our documentation.
                






                    Q: What happens if I opt out? Can I still enable Cost Anomaly Detection at a later date?
                



                    Yes, if you decide to opt out now, you will still be able to enable Cost Anomaly Detection at a later time. When you opt out, you will still be able to use Cost Explorer without Cost Anomaly Detection.
                







                    Questions?
                






                    If you have any questions regarding the information in this email or if you need additional assistance, please visit our FAQ or contact us at https://aws.amazon.com/support








                    Sincerely,
                



                    AWS Cost Management Team
                








This is an automatically generated email. Please do not reply to this email as the email address is not monitored. If you wish to stop receiving email notifications and anomaly alerts from AWS Cost Anomaly Detection, please click  here.

subject: Thank you for your Application!
body:
Hi, Adeoluwa, 

Thank you for applying to the Research Intern - Artificial Specialized Intelligence (Job number:1782950) position at Microsoft!  We're glad you're interested in a career at Microsoft and we're here to help you find a perfect fit.
 
You may not receive feedback from us on your application directly, but please know that it’s being evaluated, and you’ll hear from us as soon as the review process is complete. If you’re selected for an interview, you’ll be notified by someone on the recruiting team.
 
You can view your application status updates through your Action Center. If you see the job moved to an Archived state, that means the position is either no longer open, you withdrew from consideration, or you were not selected for the role.
 
You may notice that we move your application from one role to another. This may happen a few times and is a normal part of our recruiting process. So, if you see the job you applied to in an Archived state, and a new job listed as Active, please know that this is normal and does not negatively impact your candidacy in any way.
 
How’s your profile?
A key part of the review process is evaluating your profile in relation to the job requirements, so please make sure your profile is accurate and extensive – it’s our first step in getting to know you! You can build your profile anyway you’d like – you can import it from LinkedIn, manually update it, or import/attach a resume. The most important thing is that your profile tells your story!
 
We encourage you to check back frequently and continue to look for opportunities that match your interests, as new jobs are being posted regularly.
 
Thank you,
Microsoft Recruiting

Microsoft respects your privacy. To learn more, please read our Microsoft Data Privacy Notice.

subject: You're Invited. Apply today for $300 AWS credits
body:
Apply for $300 AWS Credits today


Based on the qualifications of your profile, you have been invited to apply for $300 in AWS credits. At AWS, we are dedicated to helping our customers find the right products and services to help them grow and scale their businesses. 
 
We want to help you build out a proof of concept that works for your business. Apply for credits to help you get started on your project. If your application is approved, the credits will be applied directly into your AWS Account.


Apply Today >




1. Fill out the form and apply for $300 in AWS credits.
2. Your application is processed within a few days.

subject: Take advantage of the AWS Free Tier
body:
Get started with AWS

Learn how to use the AWS Free Tier
The AWS Cloud has a free tier that you can use for 12 months after you create a new account. You can try some Amazon Web Services (AWS) services for free within certain usage limits.

Get to know the AWS Free Tier 


The AWS Cloud is a pay-as-you-go system where you pay only for what you use.
How to check if you are exceeding the Free Tier limit › 
How to use the AWS Free Tier and AWS Budgets to manage your AWS costs › 

Explore more than 100 products and start building on AWS using the Free Tier.
Build websites and web applications for free › 
Build a database for free › 
Build a free storage solution › 
Free machine learning services ›

Amazon PartyRock
Learn all about prompt engineering, build mini-apps, and share them with your friends ›
